{ Hey my Chessable peeps!

I am GM Ben Finegold, born in 1969 in Detroit, MI, USA. I learned chess from my dad, Ronald, who was a chess master, and my brother, Mark, also became a chess master. I am from a chess family! } { I made this Nimzo course because I played this often with Black as a kid, and I had great results. I always played } { 4…b6 , which I recommend almost exclusively for this course, and a lot of the aggressive attacking positions remind me of games in my youth. I learned the opening without a coach or books, but just by playing a lot of chess. I liked the positions where Black:
🔹played …b6, ...Bb7, ...Ne4, ...f5; and,
🔹attacked the white castled king. /img/diagrams/66044-1724655766.png

I hope everyone enjoys the course and has great results with the Nimzo-Indian! } 1... -- 
