[SourceTitle "https://www.chessable.com/variation/41576490"]

1. d4 Nf6 {[%cal Gf6e4,Re2e4][%csl Be4]} 
2. c4 e6 {[%cal Ge6d5,Gf8b4][%csl Bd5]} 
3. Nc3 Bb4 {[%cal Gb4e1][%csl Yc3,Ye1]} 
4. a3 {[%cal Ra3b4]} { The Sämisch Variation. White forces matters immediately. White loses a tempo with this move and ruins their queenside pawn structure. In compensation, White gets the two bishops and attempts to build a big center. } Bxc3+ {[%mdl 32768]} {[%csl Re1]} 
5. bxc3 b6 {[%cal Gc8b7]} { We try to play ...b7-b6 early whenever possible in the Nimzo! } 
6. Nf3 { White makes a simple developing move. This doesn't go well with 4.a3, since White could have played 4.Nf3 immediately (See the chapter on the Three Knights Variation [/course/258506/18]). } Bb7 
7. Bg5 {[%cal Rg5d8][%csl Yf6,Yd8]} h6 {[%cal Gh6g5]} 
8. Bh4 { This way of playing for White is not dangerous. If White wants to play Nf3 and Bg5, then they should do it without 4.a3. } d6 ( { 8…d6 is good since it defends the e5-square, making it more difficult for White to play e4-e5 later. } 8...g5 { is also fine. } ) 
9. e3 Nbd7 { All of Black's minor pieces are excellent! White has little compensation for their ruined queenside pawn structure. } ( 9...g5 { is already playable as well! } ) 
10. Bd3 g5! { When Black delays castling, it's usually correct to play for ...g7-g5 and castle queenside and seize the initiative! } 
11. Bg3 h5! 
12. h3 ( { A. } 12.h4?! g4 13.Nd2 Bxg2 14.Rg1 Bb7 { Black is just ahead a pawn for nothing. White also has a bad pawn structure, and the White king has no great place to go. } ) ( { B. } 12.Nxg5? h4 13.Bf4 e5 { This just wins a piece for Black. } ) h4 {[%cal Gh4g3]} 
13. Bh2 Rg8 {[%cal Ge8c8,Gd8e7][%csl Ye1,Yh2]} { Black, having the initiative on the kingside, is better. White has issues deciding what to do with their king. White's bishop on the h2-square is quite sad. Black, on the other hand, can safely castle queenside. You may play …Ne4 and ...f5 in this line, but first, I would castle queenside. If White castles soon, then …g5-g4 looks like a nice attack for us. } 
