3. Nc3 Bb4 {[%cal Gb4e1][%csl Yc3,Ye1]} 
4. f3 c5 {[%mdl 32768]} {[%cal Gc5d4]} ( { One of the few chapters where we don't play } 4...b6 { . White has insisted on playing e2-e4 very soon, so it's best to attack the d4-pawn. @@StartBlockQuote@@It's best to attack the white center before they can develop and castle. @@EndBlockQuote@@ In this chapter, in particular, we will often see that Black attacks the weak white c4-pawn with the queenside pieces. } ) 
